      • onModifyPartsSave

        public void onModifyPartsSave​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
                       throws java.io.IOException
        This method will save a part that has been modified. This method will take a selected part and allow the user to modify it. The inventory stock field must be between min and max, and max must be greater than min. It will not allow the user to save if any fields are empty or have invalid input. It will save the part as 'Outsourced' or 'In-House' based on which radio button is selected.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - The save button is clicked.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • setPartToModify

        public void setPartToModify​(Part partToModify)
        This method takes the user selected part from the 'parts' table on the 'Main Form' screen and parses the values into the correct fields. The selected part from the 'parts' table will have its values parsed into the corresponding fields. It will select the radio button based on which model class the part is an instance of. It will set the text of the last field based on the selected radio button.
        Parameters:
        partToModify - The selected part.
